To make SPI work on pi, enabled SPI (through raspi-config)
----------------------------
example code from robotics.hobbizine.com/raspiduino.html works well, except requires addition of #include <unistd.h> in order to use usleep().

- compile using >g++ -o <OUTPUTFILE> <CSOURCEFILE>
- may have to >chmod +x <FILENAME>  to make it executable
- run using >sudo ./<FILENAME>
------------------------------
Hardware
- MAKE SURE TO USE THE LOGIC LEVEL CONVERTER - NO DIRECT CONNECTIONS BETWEEN ARDUINO AND PI!!!!
	- Pi is low voltage side, Arduino is high voltage side

- We require 4 connections to each board (6 including Vcc and GND)
	- RPi MOSI (Pin 19) connects to Arduino MOSI (Pin labelled MO)
	- RPi MISO (Pin 21) connects to Arduino MISO (Pin labelled MI)
	- RPi SCLK (Pin 23) connects to Arduino SCLK (Pin labelled SCK)
	- RPi CE0  (Pin 24) connects to Arduino SS   (Pin labelled SS)
